The calls, and what may be a song (twice in the second half of the cut, after Common Cuckoo stops singing the first time, and at the begining of where the cuckoo starts again) are quite distinct from those heard by resident O.c. maculatus in Malaysia. In Malaysia this is an urban bird and one found in parks and agricultural land. In NE China and on its wintering grounds in places such as China, O.c. diffusus seems to be very much a forest bird. I am not convinced that these two are in fact the same species.
